import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'])
    ax.set_xlabel('US Gross')
    ax.set_ylabel('Worldwide Gross')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Production_Budget'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Production_Budget'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Production_Budget'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['Production_Budget'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data.values, vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, labels=data.columns)
    ax.set_xlabel('Rating')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?')
    ax.axvline(data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'].median(), color='red', label=f"Median Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating: {data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'].median():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['IMDB_Rating'].median(), color='blue', label=f"Median IMDB_Rating: {data['IMDB_Rating'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['MPAA_Rating', 'Major_Genre'])
    df = data.groupby(['MPAA_Rating', 'Major_Genre']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(df['MPAA_Rating'] + ' - ' + df['Major_Genre'], df['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('MPAA_Rating - Major_Genre')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating and Major_Genre?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
